article.description: Davidson stays tied atop the A10 with 77-66 win over GW
article.headline: Davidson stays tied atop the A10 with 77-66 win over GW
article.linkText: Davidson stays tied atop the A10 with 77-66 win over GW
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Jack Gibbs had 22 points, Brian Sullivan added 21 and Davidson beat George Washington 77-66 to stay tied for first place in the Atlantic 10. Davidson (21-6, 12-4 Atlantic 10) took its largest lead of the game at 67-51 after a 9-0 run capped by Jordan Barham's three-point play with 6:13 to go. George Washington answered with 10 straight points to get within six at 3:56, but the Colonials (18-11, 8-8) got no closer. Barham finished with 17 points and Tyler Kalinoski added 11. Davidson entered the night in a four-way tie with Dayton, Rhode Island and No. 22 Virginia Commonwealth. Rhode Island won, and Dayton's 59-55 victory over VCU knocked the Rams out of the first-place knot. The Wildcats led 32-30 at halftime but never trailed in the second. Joe McDonald had 20 points and Kevin Larsen scored 16 to lead the Colonials.
